run_abstract(25.10)                                        run_abstract(25.10)

Name
       run_abstract - Runs abstract to generate LEF from GDSII

Syntax
       run_abstract

       [-help]

       -gds_files <file_list>

       [-gen_script_only <file.il>]

       [-lib_files <file_list>]

       [-output_lef_file <file.lef>]

       [-run_script_only <file.il>]

       [-verilog_stub_files <file_list>]

       Runs  abstract to generate LEF from GDSII. The sequence of flow for the
       run_abstract command is as follows:

              * Checks if the executable "abstract" exists  in  the  path.  If
                not, it generates an error.

              * Generates "appropriate" configuration file.

              * Executes abstract with the configuration file.

              * Checks  that the "abstract" exits with an exit code of "0". If
                not, it generates an error.

       The run_abstract command is run before loading a design.

       The options for the run_abstract command  are  set  using  the  set_ab-
       stract_mode command.

       Note:

              * This  command  does not fully supports the block LEF abstract.
                Run 'ABSTRACT' standalone to generate LEF from block GDS.

              * This command is under beta control. Contact your Cadence  rep-
                resentative for more information related to this command.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each run_abstract parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man run_abstract

       -gds_files <file_list>
              Lists the GDSII files that need to be translated

              Note: It is important that only GDSII files of the same type are
              listed together.  For example, std-cells, IO  cells,  and  block
              cells should be listed in separate runs.

       -gen_script_only <file.il>
              Generates  the  SKILL  script  that can be given to the abstract
              tool but does not execute it.

       -lib_files <file_list>
              Lists liberty (.lib) files. The .lib files can also be  used  to
              define  pin  directions by using the direction from the matching
              .lib cell and pin names.

       -output_lef_file <file.lef>
              Outputs the LEF file that will have the LEF macro abstracts  but
              not technology file information.

       -run_script_only <file.il>
              Does  not  re-generate  the script but just executes it with the
              specified file.

       -verilog_stub_files <file_list>
              Can be used to define the pin directions by using the  direction
              from the matching Verilog module and pin names.

Related Information
              * set_abstract_mode

              * get_abstract_mode

